(125, 1, '2019-10-26 00:24:00', '2019-10-26 00:24:00', 'The primary function of this position is creating graphics for a vast range of marketing initiatives including: website graphics (desktop / mobile), print ads, social media, product packaging, print catalog, brochures, leaflets, etc. The ideal candidate will also possess experience and skillsets around online marketing and social media.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h4>Key Responsibilities</h4>\n<ul class=\"list-1\">\n 	<li>Cultivate a solid body of work</li>\n 	<li>Schedule project implementation and define budget constraints</li>\n 	<li>Work with a wide range of media and use graphic design software</li>\n 	<li>Think creatively and develop new design concepts, graphics and layouts</li>\n 	<li>Prepare rough drafts and present your ideas</li>\n 	<li>Amend final designs to client‚Äôs comments and gain full approval</li>\n 	<li>Work as part of a team with establishment owners, marketing professionals and operations</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\nAs was afterwards learned, the Bachelor had met with the most surprising success; all the more wonderful, for that while cruising in the same seas numerous other vessels had gone entire months without securing a single fish.', 'Senior Creative Developer', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'senior-creative-developer', '', '', '2019-10-26 00:24:00', '2019-10-26 00:24:00', '', 0, 'http://themes.loc/workscout/?post_type=job_listing&#038;p=2432', 0, 'job_listing', '', 0),
(126, 1, '2019-10-26 00:12:13', '2015-10-25 23:12:13', 'Pear US has an immediate opportunity for a part-time Marketing Coordinator in our Naperville office. This position will support the Marketing Manager and the Great Lakes Region with a variety of business development and marketing responsibilities. This position will be approximately 20 hours per week with potential beyond that depending upon performance and current business needs.\r\n\r\nThe ideal candidate will have a marketing or related bachelor‚Äôs degree and 1-3 years of experience, or 3-5 years of relevant A/E/C experience. Must be proficient with MS Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook) and Adobe Creative Suite (hands-on experience with InDesign is required, Photoshop and Acrobat Pro are preferred), possess excellent organizational and multitasking skills, be detail oriented, have knowledge of database concepts (such as Proliance and/or a CRM), excellent time management skills, a basic understanding of marketing principles, and A/E/C industry terminology and procedures. Possessing the Certified Professional Services Marketer (CPSM) designation (or the ambition to earn it) is highly preferred.\r\n\r\nWe are looking for a self-motivated individual to coordinate regional marketing activities, which include: work with technical staff to develop marketing collateral and RFQ/RFP responses, including proposal team coordination, writing, editing, design and production; plan special events (groundbreakings, ribbon cuttings and more); manage public relations efforts with regional PR consultant and corporate marketing support; interface with corporate marketing team, as needed, including updating social media and regional website information; coordinate project photography; research target markets; and be actively involved in professional and community organizations, including the Society for Marketing Professional Services (SMPS).', 'Marketing Coordinator', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'marketing-coordinator', '', '', '2019-10-26 00:12:13', '2015-10-25 23:12:13', '', 0, 'http://themes.loc/workscout/?post_type=job_listing&#038;p=2431', 0, 'job_listing', '', 0),
(127, 1, '2019-10-26 00:02:50', '2019-10-25 23:02:50', '<p class=\"margin-reset\">The Food Service Specialist ensures outstanding customer service is provided to food customers and that all food offerings meet the required stock levels and presentation standards. Beginning your career as a Food Steward will give you a strong foundation in Speedway‚Äôs food segment that can make you a vital member of the front line team!</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe <strong>Food Service Specialist</strong> will have responsibilities that include:\r\n<ul class=\"list-1\">\r\n 	<li>Executing the Food Service program, including preparing and presenting our wonderful food offerings to hungry customers on the go!</li>\r\n 	<li>Greeting customers in a friendly manner and suggestive selling and sampling items to help increase sales.</li>\r\n 	<li>Keeping our Store food area looking terrific and ready for our valued customers by managing product inventory, stocking, cleaning, etc.</li>\r\n 	<li>We‚Äôre looking for associates who enjoy interacting with people and working in a fast-paced environment!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Restaurant Team Member - Crew', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'restaurant-team-member-crew', '', '', '2019-10-26 00:02:50', '2019-10-25 23:02:50', '', 0, 'http://themes.loc/workscout/?post_type=job_listing&#038;p=2428', 0, 'job_listing', '', 0),
